  <main>
    <section id="summary">
      <h2>Project Abstract</h2>
      <p>This website project presents a visual timeline and hand-drawn illustrations of key events in the Restoration of the Gospel. The goal is to provide an engaging and spiritually uplifting experience while demonstrating key doctrinal and historical insights from REL C 225.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="timeline">
      <h2>Restoration Timeline</h2>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <h3>1820 – The First Vision</h3>
        <p>Joseph Smith prayed to know which church to join and saw God the Father and His Son, Jesus Christ. This vision marked the beginning of the Restoration.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <h3>1823 – Moroni's Visit</h3>
        <p>Moroni appeared to Joseph and told him of the gold plates which would become the Book of Mormon.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <h3>1829 – Priesthood Restoration</h3>
        <p>John the Baptist and later Peter, James, and John restored the Aaronic and Melchizedek priesthoods to Joseph Smith and Oliver Cowdery.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <h3>1830 – The Church Is Organized</h3>
        <p>The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints was officially organized on April 6, 1830.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="illustrations">
      <h2>Hand-drawn Illustrations</h2>
